1
00:01:22,220 --> 00:01:29,940
[Legend of Zang Hai]

2
00:01:30,060 --> 00:01:32,940
[Episode 16]

3
00:01:45,790 --> 00:01:47,980
Look at your furrowed brows, My Lord.

4
00:01:48,400 --> 00:01:50,410
Are you still concerned over the celestial omens?

5
00:01:54,150 --> 00:01:55,850
I went for groceries earlier today

6
00:01:56,680 --> 00:02:00,260
and heard people discussing it everywhere.

7
00:02:01,560 --> 00:02:04,490
They even mentioned you, My Lord.

8
00:02:06,840 --> 00:02:07,660
What did they say?

9
00:02:09,080 --> 00:02:10,170
They said that Zang Hai

10
00:02:10,400 --> 00:02:13,500
was bold enough to speculate on celestial omens and misled the public.

11
00:02:14,280 --> 00:02:16,890
They also said that you indulged your aide

12
00:02:17,680 --> 00:02:20,450
and failed to discipline him.

13
00:02:29,910 --> 00:02:31,890
I usually

14
00:02:32,470 --> 00:02:34,060
don't take the gossip to heart.

15
00:02:34,710 --> 00:02:36,130
But the celestial omens

16
00:02:36,800 --> 00:02:38,130
are of grave importance.

17
00:02:38,800 --> 00:02:40,850
I'm worried that if the gossip passes on

18
00:02:42,360 --> 00:02:44,570
and reaches His Majesty one day,

19
00:02:45,520 --> 00:02:49,100
someone will use it against you, My Lord.

20
00:02:56,400 --> 00:02:57,450
In my humble opinion,

21
00:02:59,080 --> 00:03:01,010
it doesn't matter whether Zang Hai was right.

22
00:03:01,590 --> 00:03:05,380
He went over your head to report the celestial omens.

23
00:03:06,470 --> 00:03:07,220
Who knows

24
00:03:08,280 --> 00:03:10,170
what he's capable of in the future?

25
00:03:10,630 --> 00:03:13,450
We can't keep someone like him around.

26
00:03:17,840 --> 00:03:19,060
You're saying...?

27
00:03:21,470 --> 00:03:22,980
If you can't bear to do it,

28
00:03:24,030 --> 00:03:26,500
I can do it for you, My Lord.

29
00:03:32,030 --> 00:03:33,450
It's easy to kill him.

30
00:03:35,960 --> 00:03:37,690
But what if the celestial omens

31
00:03:39,000 --> 00:03:39,780
prove to be true?

32
00:03:42,750 --> 00:03:45,690
In that case, it shows how well you recognize talents.

33
00:03:48,080 --> 00:03:49,290
Though talents are rare,

34
00:03:50,590 --> 00:03:53,500
the disobedient must be eliminated.

35
00:03:57,910 --> 00:03:58,570
Do you think

36
00:04:01,000 --> 00:04:02,730
that the general about to fall

37
00:04:05,840 --> 00:04:06,690
could be me?

38
00:04:09,800 --> 00:04:10,500
My Lord.

39
00:04:11,840 --> 00:04:13,610
You really believe what he said?

40
00:04:18,750 --> 00:04:21,290
Heavy rain in Zhongzhou. A blessed shower!

41
00:04:21,390 --> 00:04:22,310
Good news!

42
00:04:22,450 --> 00:04:25,280
Heavy rain in Zhongzhou. A blessed shower!

43
00:04:25,600 --> 00:04:28,290
Heavy rain in Zhongzhou. A blessed shower!

44
00:04:29,310 --> 00:04:30,550
Good news!

45
00:04:30,630 --> 00:04:33,860
Heavy rain in Zhongzhou. A blessed shower!

46
00:04:33,920 --> 00:04:37,780
[Imperial Astronomical Bureau]
Here comes His Majesty's Decree.

47
00:04:38,720 --> 00:04:42,020
Zhongzhou has suffered from drought for months,

48
00:04:42,480 --> 00:04:46,290
with rivers running dry, which is a matter of grave concern to me.

49
00:04:47,040 --> 00:04:51,850
Now, auspicious rain falls by Heaven's mercy, reviving the land,

50
00:04:52,310 --> 00:04:56,290
and relieving the people's plight, bringing universal rejoicing.

51
00:04:56,750 --> 00:04:59,850
The Imperial Astronomical Bureau foretold this blessing

52
00:05:00,310 --> 00:05:05,220
and shall be rewarded with 1000 liang of silver. By Imperial Decree.

53
00:05:05,870 --> 00:05:07,900
I, Chu Huaiming, humbly thank His Majesty.

54
00:05:25,560 --> 00:05:26,340
Gentlemen,

55
00:05:26,870 --> 00:05:28,180
we must keep working hard

56
00:05:28,950 --> 00:05:31,100
and live up to His Majesty's expectations.

57
00:05:31,600 --> 00:05:33,020
Yes, sir.

58
00:05:33,360 --> 00:05:33,980
Go back to work.

59
00:05:39,870 --> 00:05:41,100
How is Zang Hai doing?

60
00:05:41,630 --> 00:05:44,100
It's said that he's been eating and sleeping well

61
00:05:44,830 --> 00:05:47,140
and sitting around leisurely during the day

62
00:05:47,630 --> 00:05:48,770
as if nothing bothers him.

63
00:05:52,240 --> 00:05:52,980
Get back to work.

64
00:05:53,070 --> 00:05:53,540
Understood.

65
00:06:05,870 --> 00:06:06,460
Mr. Chu.

66
00:06:25,120 --> 00:06:25,810
Mr. Zang.

67
00:06:26,600 --> 00:06:28,050
You're still able to sleep?

68
00:06:28,920 --> 00:06:31,460
You'll fall into an eternal sleep in a few days.

69
00:06:31,920 --> 00:06:34,340
Cultivate yourself while you are awake

70
00:06:34,630 --> 00:06:37,050
and strive to be reincarnated into a good family.

71
00:06:38,070 --> 00:06:40,250
News says it rained in Zhongzhou,

72
00:06:40,480 --> 00:06:41,930
which is an auspicious sign.

73
00:06:42,390 --> 00:06:44,100
I won. You lost.

74
00:06:48,680 --> 00:06:50,540
Mr. Chu, what's the hurry?

75
00:06:51,720 --> 00:06:53,660
Our Lord gave me seven days.

76
00:06:54,120 --> 00:06:55,930
What's the use of even ten days?

77
00:06:56,950 --> 00:06:57,780
Don't tell me

78
00:06:58,160 --> 00:07:00,660
you still believe you can survive this.

79
00:07:03,560 --> 00:07:06,100
The Winnowing Basket Mansion heralds wind and the Net Mansion presages rain.

80
00:07:06,920 --> 00:07:07,700
You remember

81
00:07:07,870 --> 00:07:09,220
this sentence by heart.

82
00:07:10,240 --> 00:07:11,170
But I bet you haven't

83
00:07:11,390 --> 00:07:12,490
heard of this sentence.

84
00:07:14,800 --> 00:07:17,460
The moon is separated from the Net Mansion. Rain is coming.

85
00:07:18,120 --> 00:07:19,580
As the Imperial Astronomer,

86
00:07:19,920 --> 00:07:20,900
you lack expertise

87
00:07:21,390 --> 00:07:24,290
and only report good news for rewards, ignoring the facts.

88
00:07:25,040 --> 00:07:27,020
You can't even read the signs.

89
00:07:27,680 --> 00:07:30,100
Enough with your alarmist rhetoric.

90
00:07:30,480 --> 00:07:33,460
I've foretold so many auspicious omens at the bureau.

91
00:07:33,950 --> 00:07:36,000
If you don't believe me, please go back.

92
00:07:37,070 --> 00:07:38,370
No matter how eager you are,

93
00:07:38,830 --> 00:07:40,100
wait for another five days

94
00:07:41,000 --> 00:07:42,340
and see if I end up executed

95
00:07:43,000 --> 00:07:44,730
or you end up losing everything

96
00:07:45,360 --> 00:07:46,980
you have worked so hard for.

97
00:07:47,630 --> 00:07:49,810
You just won't accept your defeat, huh?

98
00:07:50,310 --> 00:07:52,020
I'm done wasting my time here.

99
00:07:52,950 --> 00:07:55,100
Just wait for the execution.

100
00:08:30,040 --> 00:08:30,460
How is the Marquis?

101
00:08:32,510 --> 00:08:34,850
Last night, my father told the household to tighten security

102
00:08:35,120 --> 00:08:36,530
and turn away all outside visitors.

103
00:08:37,200 --> 00:08:39,820
It seems that he will stay in these days.

104
00:08:41,000 --> 00:08:42,530
He looks worried.

105
00:08:43,000 --> 00:08:46,100
I'm afraid it's because of the falling star you mentioned.

106
00:08:46,840 --> 00:08:48,490
Why would you say something like that?

107
00:08:49,720 --> 00:08:51,010
To save my life, of course.

108
00:08:51,960 --> 00:08:53,010
It was a critical moment.

109
00:08:53,360 --> 00:08:54,700
If I hadn't made up something dramatic,

110
00:08:55,080 --> 00:08:56,980
your father would have killed me on the spot.

111
00:08:58,720 --> 00:08:59,940
So I came up with that statement

112
00:09:00,510 --> 00:09:02,180
to get myself out of trouble.

113
00:09:03,840 --> 00:09:05,610
Generals and ministers die every year.

114
00:09:06,200 --> 00:09:07,770
Strange weather occurs every year.

115
00:09:08,480 --> 00:09:10,010
I only mentioned a falling star

116
00:09:10,510 --> 00:09:12,220
without specifying the rank of that person.

117
00:09:14,030 --> 00:09:15,460
It was just to fool your father.

118
00:09:19,030 --> 00:09:20,460
If he knew he had been restless

119
00:09:20,790 --> 00:09:22,130
because of your lie,

120
00:09:22,750 --> 00:09:23,460
he'd kill you.

121
00:09:24,240 --> 00:09:25,580
I only need a few more days

122
00:09:26,270 --> 00:09:27,460
to prove

123
00:09:28,120 --> 00:09:28,850
that I'm right.

124
00:09:32,000 --> 00:09:32,460
Young Master.

125
00:09:33,550 --> 00:09:34,250
Do me a favor.

126
00:09:34,840 --> 00:09:37,010
Get your father's former subordinates

127
00:09:37,550 --> 00:09:38,820
to give warnings to Zhongzhou.

128
00:09:40,630 --> 00:09:41,100
Alright.

129
00:09:45,080 --> 00:09:45,940
I need another favor

130
00:09:46,480 --> 00:09:47,250
from you.

131
00:09:51,790 --> 00:09:52,820
Stay alert these days.

132
00:09:53,270 --> 00:09:54,890
No one shall enter with weapons.

133
00:10:02,390 --> 00:10:02,940
My Lord.

134
00:10:03,480 --> 00:10:05,650
It's been raining in Zhongzhou for three days.

135
00:10:05,950 --> 00:10:07,410
The drought has eased.

136
00:10:07,540 --> 00:10:08,630
Everything is in order.

137
00:10:10,670 --> 00:10:12,010
It's been three days.

138
00:10:13,030 --> 00:10:13,980
How big is the rain?

139
00:10:14,910 --> 00:10:17,130
It shows no sign of letting up.

140
00:10:22,910 --> 00:10:24,820
Go to the Ministry of Works every day

141
00:10:25,240 --> 00:10:27,370
to inquire about it from the Hydrological Bureau.

142
00:10:43,720 --> 00:10:44,190
My Lord.

143
00:10:44,720 --> 00:10:46,370
It's been raining for four days,

144
00:10:46,600 --> 00:10:48,130
with the largest rainfall in a decade.

145
00:10:48,390 --> 00:10:49,340
Water is starting

146
00:10:49,670 --> 00:10:51,060
to gather at the terrain.

147
00:10:52,510 --> 00:10:53,060
Go back to work.

148
00:11:05,440 --> 00:11:07,100
It's been raining heavily for five days,

149
00:11:07,200 --> 00:11:08,730
with rivers flooding

150
00:11:09,000 --> 00:11:10,060
and rocks falling from mountains,

151
00:11:10,060 --> 00:11:12,530
destroying a dozen houses and injuring nearly 100 people.

152
00:11:14,560 --> 00:11:15,450
Keep me updated.

153
00:11:15,790 --> 00:11:17,530
It's been raining for six days.

154
00:11:17,620 --> 00:11:19,130
The water levels of nine rivers are rising.

155
00:11:19,670 --> 00:11:21,580
We've sent someone to strengthen the dam.

156
00:11:22,080 --> 00:11:23,940
If it keeps raining for two or three days,

157
00:11:25,270 --> 00:11:27,340
I'm afraid the dam will break.

158
00:11:34,030 --> 00:11:34,700
No way.

159
00:11:36,840 --> 00:11:37,460
No way.

160
00:11:43,750 --> 00:11:44,250
Mr. Chu.

161
00:11:46,750 --> 00:11:49,370
Mr. Zhuang, please tell the Marquis

162
00:11:49,750 --> 00:11:50,770
that I need to see him.

163
00:11:51,240 --> 00:11:52,980
My Lord has been ill these days

164
00:11:53,200 --> 00:11:55,820
and has stopped receiving visitors.

165
00:11:56,500 --> 00:11:58,300
Mr. Chu, please go back.

166
00:12:09,480 --> 00:12:10,340
Why?

167
00:12:15,670 --> 00:12:16,580
On what ground?

168
00:12:22,790 --> 00:12:23,490
Zang Hai.

169
00:12:24,000 --> 00:12:25,220
I wish you die!

170
00:12:50,150 --> 00:12:50,730
What did

171
00:12:53,150 --> 00:12:54,100
Mr. Cao say?

172
00:12:54,360 --> 00:12:55,340
He said

173
00:12:56,000 --> 00:12:58,460
that you should apologize to His Majesty as soon as possible.

174
00:12:59,480 --> 00:13:01,180
Mr. Cao is not going to save me?

175
00:13:02,720 --> 00:13:03,850
He can't just abandon me.

176
00:13:03,870 --> 00:13:04,730
Master said

177
00:13:05,240 --> 00:13:06,650
that with the relentless rainfall in Zhongzhou,

178
00:13:07,240 --> 00:13:08,370
His Majesty hasn't slept well lately

179
00:13:08,870 --> 00:13:10,530
and has barely eaten for days.

180
00:13:11,720 --> 00:13:12,530
Mr. Chu.

181
00:13:12,960 --> 00:13:15,490
You read the omens wrong and endangered the people.

182
00:13:15,960 --> 00:13:16,940
You are on your own.

183
00:13:29,200 --> 00:13:30,700
Father, he left.

184
00:13:33,670 --> 00:13:34,710
Zang Hai...

185
00:13:35,320 --> 00:13:36,340
It's him again.

186
00:13:38,030 --> 00:13:40,650
He even went after the Imperial Astronomer.

187
00:13:42,550 --> 00:13:44,180
Imperial Astronomer...

188
00:13:47,580 --> 00:13:49,380
[Confinement Chamber]

189
00:13:56,840 --> 00:13:57,580
Greetings, Mr. Chu.

190
00:13:59,720 --> 00:14:00,460
Zang Hai,

191
00:14:02,030 --> 00:14:03,220
don't you look great?

192
00:14:04,320 --> 00:14:06,530
How can you be so confident?

193
00:14:11,150 --> 00:14:12,530
Judging from your look,

194
00:14:13,030 --> 00:14:15,460
I bet it has been raining in Zhongzhou for days,

195
00:14:16,120 --> 00:14:17,130
which caused floods.

196
00:14:22,200 --> 00:14:22,890
Zang Hai.

197
00:14:23,630 --> 00:14:25,220
You are the Marquis's aide.

198
00:14:25,630 --> 00:14:27,250
I also work for the Marquis.

199
00:14:27,910 --> 00:14:29,850
We are in the same boat.

200
00:14:30,600 --> 00:14:32,180
We shouldn't fight each other.

201
00:14:34,120 --> 00:14:36,340
If you want to be an official,

202
00:14:37,080 --> 00:14:38,980
I can put in a good word

203
00:14:39,240 --> 00:14:39,890
with our Lord.

204
00:14:40,670 --> 00:14:41,940
If you want money,

205
00:14:42,480 --> 00:14:43,460
I can help you.

206
00:14:43,870 --> 00:14:45,820
How much do you want? Name a price.

207
00:14:47,200 --> 00:14:47,650
Zang Hai.

208
00:14:48,750 --> 00:14:49,370
Zang Hai.

209
00:14:53,320 --> 00:14:55,250
You only have to tell our Lord

210
00:14:55,840 --> 00:14:56,980
that the celestial omens

211
00:14:57,600 --> 00:14:58,580
carry mixed messages.

212
00:14:59,360 --> 00:15:00,580
I read the auspicious part

213
00:15:00,870 --> 00:15:01,980
and you the ominous part.

214
00:15:02,550 --> 00:15:03,940
We were both correct.

215
00:15:05,080 --> 00:15:06,490
We just didn't foresee it all.

216
00:15:07,200 --> 00:15:07,890
In that case,

217
00:15:08,000 --> 00:15:09,300
I'll just be punished for negligence

218
00:15:09,320 --> 00:15:10,490
and you will get to live.

219
00:15:10,910 --> 00:15:11,980
It's a win-win.

220
00:15:12,480 --> 00:15:13,060
What do you think?

221
00:15:17,750 --> 00:15:18,460
Mr. Chu.

222
00:15:20,120 --> 00:15:21,100
Are you begging me?

223
00:15:31,630 --> 00:15:32,610
I lack expertise

224
00:15:33,080 --> 00:15:34,650
and read the celestial omens wrong.

225
00:15:35,320 --> 00:15:35,940
Mr. Zang.

226
00:15:36,390 --> 00:15:37,940
I recommended you

227
00:15:38,030 --> 00:15:39,490
to the Marquis.

228
00:15:40,840 --> 00:15:43,650
Since we are both serving our Lord,

229
00:15:43,840 --> 00:15:44,580
help me out.

230
00:15:46,000 --> 00:15:47,460
In return, I'll go through

231
00:15:47,750 --> 00:15:49,850
any hardship for you whenever you need me.

232
00:15:52,080 --> 00:15:52,940
Honestly, Mr. Chu.

233
00:15:53,910 --> 00:15:55,460
All those offers

234
00:15:55,980 --> 00:15:57,420
sound highly tempting.

235
00:15:57,480 --> 00:15:58,100
Right?

236
00:15:59,000 --> 00:15:59,700
Then let's...

237
00:15:59,750 --> 00:16:02,130
But what's wrong is wrong.

238
00:16:03,000 --> 00:16:05,100
If all the right and wrong, true and false,

239
00:16:05,440 --> 00:16:08,010
and good and evil can be altered in this world,

240
00:16:08,840 --> 00:16:10,940
it would be against my parents' teachings

241
00:16:11,600 --> 00:16:13,650
and the court's discipline and laws.

242
00:16:16,240 --> 00:16:16,770
Mr. Chu.

243
00:16:17,670 --> 00:16:19,100
This play has started.

244
00:16:19,720 --> 00:16:21,610
How can we stop halfway?

245
00:16:22,000 --> 00:16:22,530
Zang Hai.

246
00:16:23,150 --> 00:16:24,700
You're determined to destroy me?

247
00:16:25,390 --> 00:16:26,770
There's no bad blood between us.

248
00:16:27,550 --> 00:16:29,370
Why do you want me dead so badly?

249
00:16:29,790 --> 00:16:33,060
So you know that there's no bad blood between us.

250
00:16:34,240 --> 00:16:35,890
Then why did you try to kill me

251
00:16:36,080 --> 00:16:38,530
again and again at the Late Emperor's Mausoleum?

252
00:16:39,960 --> 00:16:41,460
You caught those folk people

253
00:16:41,720 --> 00:16:43,490
and made them "feng shui masters".

254
00:16:44,240 --> 00:16:46,700
Those craftsmen died tragically in the mausoleum.

255
00:16:47,480 --> 00:16:49,580
You shoved the burning charcoal down that girl's throat.

256
00:16:50,000 --> 00:16:51,220
You stepped on the innocent

257
00:16:51,270 --> 00:16:52,490
to get ahead.

258
00:16:52,510 --> 00:16:53,940
What have they done to you?

259
00:17:03,200 --> 00:17:03,850
Mr. Chu.

260
00:17:04,830 --> 00:17:06,530
You are the Imperial Astronomer.

261
00:17:07,480 --> 00:17:10,220
You know all about reincarnation

262
00:17:10,720 --> 00:17:12,290
and karma, don't you?

263
00:17:16,480 --> 00:17:19,250
You came to show off your power last time.

264
00:17:19,920 --> 00:17:20,770
But this time,

265
00:17:21,880 --> 00:17:23,460
did you come to ask for help

266
00:17:24,830 --> 00:17:26,220
or say goodbye to me?

267
00:17:31,070 --> 00:17:31,570
You have

268
00:17:32,590 --> 00:17:33,810
foreseen everything.

269
00:17:35,400 --> 00:17:37,460
But have you foreseen the fact

270
00:17:38,790 --> 00:17:39,810
that you'll die today?

271
00:17:43,400 --> 00:17:44,010
Chu Huaiming.

272
00:17:44,830 --> 00:17:46,010
You misread the celestial omens.

273
00:17:46,350 --> 00:17:48,660
In the worst case, you'll be demoted and imprisoned.

274
00:17:48,880 --> 00:17:51,250
You'll be able to start anew in a few years.

275
00:17:52,270 --> 00:17:53,460
But if you kill me,

276
00:17:54,880 --> 00:17:56,570
you have to pay with your life.

277
00:18:00,310 --> 00:18:01,700
Pay with my life?

278
00:18:03,720 --> 00:18:06,380
You killed Yang Zhen and Qu Jiao.

279
00:18:06,640 --> 00:18:08,180
You should pay with your life, too.

280
00:18:08,880 --> 00:18:10,620
